AB  - The research on the social support environmental network of the empty-nest elderly is of great significance to the sustainable development of urban civilization. In order to explore the characteristics of the urban empty-nest elderly's social support network and its impact on the willingness of the community care for the elderly. In this paper, the binary logistic regression analysis was used to explore the characteristics of the emotional network and social network scale, network relationship composition, network heterogeneity and their impact on the willingness of the community care for the elderly, from the perspective of the ecosystem. The results show that the social network of urban empty-nest elderly is dominated by strong ties. The homogeneity of the professional class (OR=0.193) and education level (OR=0.095) of the members of the emotional network has a negative predictive effect on the willingness of the empty-nest elderly. The differences in the educational level (0R-3.225) of social network members have a positive predictive effect on the willingness of the empty-nest elderly, while the differences in gender (OR=0.286), age (OR=0.108) and occupational class (OR=0.015) have a negative predictive effects on community willingness to provide for the elderly. The proportion of weak tics (OR=7.987) in the actual help network has a positive predictive effect on the willingness, while the convergence of education level (OR=0.148) will have a negative effect on the willingness. The results show that the interaction between the ecosystem community and the environment brings new enlightenment to the willingness of the community care for the elderly. In addition to the traditional concept of population, family and social security factors, the interaction of the social environmental network of the elderly will also have an impact on the community's willingness.
